                              <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                Have you ever felt your hands trembling, voice shaking and breath uneven whenever it is your time to give a presentation in front of the entire class? The experience of interacting with a large audience can be quite nerve-wracking. However, mastering the art of effective communication is not an impossible endeavour. 

                                </p>
                                <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                                    Communicating confidently among large audiences is an exceptional skill that everyone should inculcate and benefit from. Regardless of the profession, you decide to undertake, being proficient at communicating will always give you an edge and help you easily participate in meetings and conferences! So, without further ado, here are a few tips you can try to improve your communication skills:
    
                                    </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';"><li>●	Gain a Realistic Perspective on Self-Love </li>
                                  <li>●	Be an Active Listener </li>
                                  <li>●	Practice in Front of the Mirror</li>
                                  <li>●	Keep a Few Points Ready</li>
                                  <li>●	Start with Little Content   </li>
                                  <li>●	Cover a Wide Range of Topics </li>
                                  <li>●	Gradually Increase the Size of Your Audience </li>
                                  <li>●	Be Mindful of Your Gestures and Body Language </li>
                                  <li>●	Hone your Fluency and Voice Modulation</li>
                                  <li>●	Start Practicing with Simple Vocabulary </li>
                                  <li>●	Learn from Your Mistakes </li>
                                
                                  	</ul> 
                                  
                              </p>
                              <div class="row" >
                                <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                    <img alt="Studing organising workshop with confidence" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/How%20to%20Improve%20Your%20Communication%20Skills%3F%2F3765669.jpg?alt=media&token=9caa4ea4-411a-4be0-8274-7f9411945a18" >
