  <H3 style=" font-style: underline">9. <u>Start Practicing with Simple Vocabulary:
</u>
</H3>
<p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
    While practising your communication skills, it is better to stick to words that you are comfortable with than experiment with new and unfamiliar terms that might make you nervous while speaking. You can gradually build your vocabulary by learning a few new words at a time. Please remember that you need not necessarily use jargon to make your speech engaging. You can communicate effectively and confidently while using simple words as well. 
</p>

<H3 style=" font-style: underline">10. <u>Learn from Your Mistakes:
</u>
</H3>
<p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
    Last but not least, learn from your mistakes and errors and don’t let them bog you down. Keep practising and learn from your mistakes. You are the best judge of your abilities, and the more you learn from your mistakes, the closer you get to becoming the confident orator you visualise yourself to be! 
    

